The paper describes a deep neural network-based method for segmenting brain regions of interest with minimal human supervision. This involves image processing and analysis, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep learning also suggests that the paper could belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of automated methods, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the development of an atlas, which could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of imaging modalities, which could fall under the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
